To create an interestingly new task family, I'll focus on measuring the model's ability to understand and apply scientific principles in practical scenarios. This will involve designing tasks that require the agent to explain scientific phenomena and apply scientific concepts to solve real-world problems. This capability hasn't been directly measured in the previous task families, and it can reveal both the depth of the model's scientific knowledge and its ability to reason through complex scenarios. I will use the LLM judge to evaluate the correctness and completeness of the explanations and solutions.

